## Context

- GSE134809 pipeline fully executed: 97,152 cells × 22,625 genes from 31 samples (Martin et al. Cell 2019)
- Pipeline: download → QC (min_genes≥500, mito<20%, MAD outlier) → normalize → HVG/PCA/UMAP/Leiden → annotation (21 cell types) → IL-23/Th17 pathway scoring (6 modules) → DE (10 cell types) → regulon (739 TFs)
- Scrublet skipped (macOS ARM bus error); used MAD-based outlier filtering
- data_loader.py needed workaround: RAW.tar has flat per-sample 10x files, not sub-archives. Also: PANDAS_FUTURE_INFER_STRING=0 required for h5ad write with pandas 3 + anndata 0.12.6

## Key Findings
- Th17 top IL-23 responder (mean=0.1654, 84.9% pos), ILC3 second (mean=0.0591, 61.5% pos)
- FCGR1A/IL23A co-expression in myeloid is RARE (0.3%) — distinct populations. Guselkumab dual-mechanism targets separate compartments.
- IL12B too sparse for causal anchor. CXCL9 co-localizes with IL-23 myeloid (18.4% in Inflammatory_Mac)
- CIITA/MHC-II regulon dominates myeloid TF activity — potential novel IL-23 regulatory axis
- DE: Th17 upregulates RORA in IL-23-high samples (confirms biology), Inflammatory_Mac has 327 DE genes

